2ArTlg=w224-h398-k-no"},{"title":"Videos","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEVmmQvQEJe8DlMDZusfIGbGtwiqHArIhzoPUI9zyspKM8yFwAGicsrbClCB7pUd3iID1XSdxSa1pZH5n3UIhdBTYexN731VCN5Wr8sQf72U6czecLVQSi8H-Z1-UQonQ95fnD2-wfyhN0=w224-h398-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=OgimALORcqxZygRAkGbe4w\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=139.84698\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://book.modento.io/moritis-dentistry/g/google-schedule-link?rwg_token=AFd1xnEBwJ816z-4CNKWMvqTABuoUlN-jlXKh7PIzc7YrIGwCQWX3ShJZ2c98xv3tQaEM8v7P5vAts-dI9MTlbDtOpClfXcu9Q%3D%3D","source":"modento.io"}],"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://www.moritisdentistry.com/our-services/%3Futm_source%3Dgoogle%26utm_medium%3Dlocal%26utm_campaign%3Dgbpservices\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwjInaWvur-UAxXgmO4BHRJ2EGIQqRkIHygS\u0026usg=AOvVaw2zDvrAq-VjbUU72UT11Qc-","source":"moritisdentistry.com"},"owner":{"id":"116377360758911097050","name":"Moritis Shin Dentistry of Seattle (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116377360758911097050"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"509 Olive Wy #1520","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Riddhi Bhide","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrpEwAmgFcEVxxjmAr3t81aOwS6kY1otAPTJLKuuZEj5nYbGxRqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently took my one-year-old for their very first dental appointment at Mortis Shin Dentistry  of Seattle and I couldn't be more impressed. From the moment we walked in, the front desk staff and the hygienist were absolutely delightful and made my child feel so comfortable. I had been bracing myself for tears and screaming—especially since my little one has recently become very protective of their mouth—but the experience was the complete opposite.\nDr. Shin and the entire team were incredibly patient. Even though it took a while for my child to feel ready to open up, they never rushed us; they simply waited and stayed encouraging. It is so reassuring to find a practice that is truly family-oriented and handles all age groups with such care. Plus, the central location is a huge bonus—it's wonderful not having to drive miles for such high-quality care for a child as young as one. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rainbows2Rain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoDTA46asvt7DkyDOswxFbCx_WGvjfKOWtPPdICuK65HYxQtM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Shin and his team are excellent. They are skilled at what they do, and seem to really prioritize patient comfort. During my last cleaning I was  so relaxed that my oura ring thought I took a 30 minute nap. They do not try to  “upsell” with unnecessary procedures like many other dentists unfortunately do, and their Invisalign pricing is very fair.  Dr. Shin is young, highly trained and takes the time to ask questions/listen to patients.i completely trust his judgement and his technical skills, and the hygienists are the best I’ve ever experienced. Parking is easy on the surface lot by the building or at Pacific Place. There is valet parking for the building if needed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jimin Yoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUL4N8crCmyljqXcKOTEpF3DHPBcp41eN4tHKFS94qAZrhMS0FJrw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had such a great experience with Dr. Shin! He helped me with my broken molar and root canal, and the whole process was completely painless. He was very gentle, kind, and made sure I felt comfortable the entire time. I really appreciated his professionalism and care — I highly recommend Dr. Shin 👍👍👍","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"T S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGiEkyCw1bUql-vcbSb3MYQoPpc2ajVQve4nyszxf-pBRa439N=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have a hard time feeling comfortable at the dentist so I’ve been looking for a dentist who is convenient to me and that I feel comfortable with. From the first visit, I’ve been so pleased. The staff is extremely kind and patient and Dr Shin is wonderful. He takes time to talk you through things, gives you options and recommendations but most importantly, he starts by asking me about what I want. This has been the biggest difference. With a lot of my other dentists I often feel that if I don’t comply with their recommendation, it makes it awkward to continue seeing them. Not with Dr Shin. He is also very thorough, gentle and very caring. The hygienists are the same and I can tell from their rapport, that Dr Shin treats them as peers and not just subordinates.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Antwan Williams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLXNp98hU6iDXA1hESn7QO0W40vWJ2JcBayawidnyKwFa04dc4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"One thing I care about-- is my experience. I can confidently say that, Breanna, I believe shes the office manager did her due diligence to ensure I had a horrible experience.\n\nI came in for an issue with anticipation of getting all of my work done here at the office. I had some changes with work, which means that I couldn't be there due to business needs and lets be honest, in this economy we are prioritizing work. Also, I wasn't in any agony or pain at the moment. I reached out on the 22nd saying that I would not be able to make it due to work. My appointment was on the 24th. This is a office that is only open Monday-Thurday so it's super hard to give that notice during business hours. She didn't try to understand anything that I was saying, she didn't try to hear me out, just flat out said no. Emergencies happen all the time. No one will be able to make all appointments and other things will take priority. I truly hate the way I was treated and 100% will not be spending my resources here.\n\nI hope the $150 fee was worth the thousands that I was planning to pay to fix my smile. Again, I care about my experience, how I am being treated, and how someone helps me navigate in a space that I am not a SME in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ariel van Spronsen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXig7SWUu7gto24j-Nbw4tG54uylrz5qJb7n4o2xicejusUz9IGfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was a patient of Dr. Alan Moritis for over 20 years, and continued with his daughter Dr. Julia Moritis when she took over the practice. Now under the care of Dr. Harry Shin, I continue to be a happy patient. I appreciate their measured approach to dental care - they don’t push procedures unnecessarily but are also proactive when they’re needed. The docs explain things well and always involve me in decision-making. The office is clean and up to date, and the views from their 15th floor downtown office aren’t too shabby either! I also appreciate that they invest in technologies that are purposeful rather than trendy, so If you’re looking for maximum technology bling I’d say look at other practices.\n\nBecause of the great preventive care I’ve received here over the last 25+ years I haven’t had many restorative  procedures, but the one root canal and two fillings I’ve done here were painless and complication-free.\n\nI highly recommend Moritis Shin Dentistry. solid, thoughtful, trustworthy lifelong dental care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hyunju Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLqVlwusyglQ1hk2QwVZo4HDYAl9k69On_TDzUoIzaX8tYOuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Shin is truly an exceptional dentist — kind, gentle, and incredibly thorough. He takes the time to explain every step of the process and makes you feel completely at ease, even during more involved procedures. His attention to detail and calm demeanor create an environment of trust and comfort, and it’s clear he genuinely cares about his patients’ well-being. I always leave feeling confident that I’ve received the highest level of care. I’m so glad to have found Dr. Shin and wouldn’t hesitate to recommend him to anyone looking for a compassionate and skilled dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Becca Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUX0KYadtU-6GSitEh5c4EILSVfAVBk4h7d-_mA5ixCWLktBYs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent practice with attentive, caring staff whose tenure has spanned multiple decades with our family. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"4985f8da-4737-4e98-ba46-d0d63c0325fb","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Seattle+Smiles+Dental/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x54906ab39321aca9:0x5f41109262d6c9df!8m2!3d47.6088291!4d-122.3357842!16s%2Fg%2F1hhw12l48!19sChIJqawhk7NqkFQR38nWYpIQQV8?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"6863785527998859743","title":"Seattle Smiles Dental","categories":["Dentist"],"category":"Dentist","address":"1325 4th Ave #1230, Seattle, WA 98101","open_hours":{"Friday":["Closed"],"Monday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["Closed"],"Tuesday":["8 AM–4 PM"],"Wednesday":["8 AM–4 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"http://www.seattlesmilesdental.com/","phone":"(206) 624-1773","plus_code":"JM57+GM Seattle, Washington","review_count":56,"review_rating":4.5,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":6,"2":2,"3":0,"4":0,"5":48},"latitude":47.6088291,"longtitude":-122.33578419999999,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHFJxwfD6qsXBBUbwE2iLQmTzsuFwDgwue73kzHbwKTMOCFlBzHtvpCoPiFhA0EUNLkme6UX2gkKxLJ6zHhZgVyopGkPZYnKN9HqBE6B8pSAMsVo5SN6Mz46lSkJhG1b9ApirKv=w408-h272-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x54906ab39321aca9:0x5f41109262d6c9df","place_id":"ChIJqawhk7NqkFQR38nWYpIQQV8","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHFJxwfD6qsXBBUbwE2iLQmTzsuFwDgwue73kzHbwKTMOCFlBzHtvpCoPiFhA0EUNLkme6UX2gkKxLJ6zHhZgVyopGkPZYnKN9HqBE6B8pSAMsVo5SN6Mz46lSkJhG1b9ApirKv=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAGxUZP_Gp7Lu4KOnvbpgseE9Om5OEa29mgURUNy-MTMMvqCaH-yOOTtSfwDO21Kbv3Civ566btcfT_xdZ4iYxnLRfdWyMqOGDM1Dp7qxZnr8RGg1cGVwH10PmYNIE311JWJbvRU=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=aVreBSYLtGrjpZQCZBAThg\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=118.63215\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"115627932111801967114","name":"Seattle Smiles Dental (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115627932111801967114"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"1325 4th Ave #1230","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"from_the_business","name":"From the business","options":[{"name":"Identifies as Asian-owned","enabled":true},{"name":"Identifies as women-owned","enabled":true}]},{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible seating","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true}]},{"id":"children","name":"Children","options":[{"name":"Nursing room","enabled":true}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Lanette Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKg0hRBdHegdMwVsSzwYGxA0wcKlb4E_rV1TP-h_ZQkUfYi5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I went to this office a couple of times when they still accepted my insurance (Premera Blue Cross). At first, I really liked them. The staff were friendly, the view from the chairs was beautiful, and they even offered nitrous oxide, which I appreciated.\n\nUnfortunately, my experience changed after they stopped accepting my insurance. I had already booked a cleaning appointment, so I went ahead even though coverage was limited. During that visit, the hygienist suggested that I might as well stay with them because my insurance might not work well elsewhere—which felt more like a sales pitch than genuine advice.\n\nThey told me I had three cavities and implied that it was because I hadn’t chosen an optional fluoride treatment they recommended previously. I later went to another dentist (who does take my insurance) and brought the paperwork over. That dentist personally examined me and told me I had no cavities—just a few areas to watch. It really seemed like the original office was exaggerating or inventing problems to make money, which was disappointing and felt unethical.\n\nWhen I asked if they had recommendations for other dentists that took Premera, they told me to just look online, which wasn’t very warm or helpful either.\n\nOverall: if you have insurance they accept, you might have a decent experience. But based on what happened to me, I would be very cautious about trusting their treatment recommendations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rachael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUevc9f_malpG_X48VyOqD7DOnIlZCdJQVGjpzhHGsEuvkJ2ZfYNA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you have sensitive teeth and anxiety at the dentist, Seattle Smiles is the perfect place for all of your care. Not only is Dr. Nguyen a terrific and understanding dentist, but my hygienist, Lisa, is extremely gentle and caring. She warmed the cleaning water and took her time to make sure I was comfortable. The office is small and peaceful with an amazing view. I wish more people with dental anxiety could find this office for care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oz Harb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViFj0-9DH4YEVZuLRgZaP1tbXGOxTKHiXN6JdmzqypQ9Duqmhzyg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful great people. The staff is all friendly and professional and the office has beautiful views.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jesse Grooms","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7OQziX9-SaJyYpaHA_PoFVZ93jR3OpzMnpvFnSI1UXIzbCw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Seattle Smiles Dental, Dr. Nguyen, offers an exceptional experience. From the moment you walk in, her office staff and assistants are welcoming, professional, and attentive. I initially visited for Invisalign but was impressed by the thorough consultation, where Dr. Nguyen presented alternative options like porcelain crowns to address my gaps and spaces. Additionally, I expressed interest in Botox, and we had a thoughtful discussion about the process and expected results. I decided to proceed and am completely satisfied with the outcome. Dr. Nguyen is meticulous, taking the time to explain every detail and ensuring you feel prepared and comfortable throughout the entire process. I highly recommend her for both dental and cosmetic treatments!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDzhLVY-cxLQOYremkfrl68fpVtfbn5bv2qA04ORwFyVyvrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone who works here is so kind! I have severe dental anxiety and none of the staff makes me feel embarrassed about it at all. They are helping me be more comfortable at the dentist every time, I would recommend them to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Tai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTRC1X0l-Agr1S7StRq6Mh-37EjAxuyerDeTLGYWxVOHdTta-w1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been a patient for nearly a decade, and this dentist office consistently impresses. The hygienists excel at leaving my mouth feeling refreshingly clean. Dr. Nguyen is attentive, gentle, and provides valuable recommendations. Plus, the predominantly female staff adds a welcoming touch to the overall experience. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"G/Johnny Gannardal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWx45211H4BLabqL0nssvBcoxX7taoJ4BVKA_j0FmPA60sRoU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From start to finish I genuinely enjoyed my experience at Seattle Smiles. The staff is super friendly and always willing to go above and beyond to provide quality service to their patience. Scheduling appointments is easy, rescheduling is possible, and the warm greeting when you walk in the door is greatly appreciated!\n\nI personally enjoy the beautiful views of the city from the dental chair and the top notch service provided by Dr. Nguyen and her crew. I would TOTALLY suggest this office for anyone looking for a clean office that is customer friendly and on point with their service. :D","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ruth Haney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-DHrnI-zIjg6igL1PXjNBoxRkNohKfQDMNlP1YlcXyYqzrlRw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been a patient at Seattle Smiles for over two years, and my experiences have been so consistently great that I felt compelled to acknowledge the team there in a review. Over the past two years, I’ve had regular cleanings, an emergency crown, a complete Invisalign treatment, whitening, and probably at least one other thing I’m forgetting - the team at Seattle Smiles is always a pleasure to interact with. Dr. Nguyen is professional and personable and put me at ease right away, as did her assistant Josie. They both are really great.  I appreciate how thorough Dr. Nguyen is at explaining what’s going on and what the options are.  I also feel like she and the team advocate for me with my terrible insurance company.  Alison is an amazing dental hygienist and makes me not dread having my teeth cleaned. I don’t know if it’s possible to actually enjoy a cleaning, but this is probably as close as you can get!  I also had a great experience with Dr. Asmeret, who saw me for a time sensitive appointment on a day that Dr. Nguyen was out.  Whomever I see, I feel like the experience is always seamless, which is a testament to how well the team works together. And finally, a special shout out to Brittany, who manages the front office. I really appreciate that I can book appointments and ask questions via email, and Brittany is super responsive and friendly with her correspondence. This office is good vibes all the way around. Oh, and the office itself – the design is neutral, professional, and welcoming. Beyond having a good experience at my appointments, I feel like my teeth and smile look their best under the care of this team.  Win/win!  Thank you, Seattle Smiles!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"4985f8da-4737-4e98-ba46-d0d63c0325fb","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Seattle+Sound+Dental+-+Downtown/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x549015794c9d9df1:0xc7317534234b966!8m2!3d47.6127286!4d-122.3366087!16s%2Fg%2F11b6bbzbmh!19sChIJ8Z2dTHkVkFQRZrk0QlMXcww?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"897086397137336678","title":"Seattle Sound Dental - Downtown","categories":["Dentist","Cosmetic dentist","Dental clinic","Dental hygienist","Dental implants periodontist","Emergency dental service","Endodontist","Oral surgeon","Orthodontist"],"category":"Dentist","address":"509 Olive Wy #1024, Seattle, WA 98101","open_hours":{"Friday":["8 AM–5 PM"],"Monday":["Closed"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["8 AM–2 PM"],"Tuesday":["8 AM–7 PM"],"Wednesday":["8 AM–7 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"https://seattlesounddental.com/?utm_source=gmb\u0026utm_medium=organic\u0026utm_campaign=listing","phone":"(206) 774-5206","plus_code":"JM77+39 Seattle, Washington","review_count":460,"review_rating":4.9,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":10,"2":4,"3":0,"4":10,"5":436},"latitude":47.6127286,"longtitude":-122.3366087,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHE_YO1Pt7LS-mwwjjBCrWPARAGB5Q5fpgQZx4Dw6fGjhBbu2DSthkwjvamwB1HhAwp9a38aZf76q4PvqJzk6DigqvhUmR5jXU6gT-2qaoP1rI-RNhOyYW9pg3-Q_454VcUpnSP-g=w426-h240-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x549015794c9d9df1:0xc7317534234b966","place_id":"ChIJ8Z2dTHkVkFQRZrk0QlMXcww","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHE_YO1Pt7LS-mwwjjBCrWPARAGB5Q5fpgQZx4Dw6fGjhBbu2DSthkwjvamwB1HhAwp9a38aZf76q4PvqJzk6DigqvhUmR5jXU6gT-2qaoP1rI-RNhOyYW9pg3-Q_454VcUpnSP-g=w529-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAF76vGdTrjjq79R2cqiHdl3TajOy314kBv8uWIwnYF36NGgxwGlqyvVNjPET9ynGWK8nLq9QNowa-HXrDUBtv77EtzqzuQ5kmVcdiMQKlMbPh5-5ITGc4y1ymwFvDADYjiLnfsS=w224-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=OgimALORcqxZygRAkGbe4w\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=135.96869\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://seattlesounddental.com/\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwicw-Kvur-UAxVLr-4BHTsINxEQqRkIICgT\u0026usg=AOvVaw10Fv2XQWq8qyI6d8GPsGMU","source":"seattlesounddental.com"},"owner":{"id":"111703910555880372048","name":"Seattle Sound Dental - Downtown (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111703910555880372048"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"509 Olive Wy #1024","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Kafiya Arte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQJcM7mlj6fzpq0_AsBFQc6kVkJKCsR8UVirxLG46t6gELCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Two of my siblings and two of my close friends receive their dental care through Dr. Tanner. They rave about him all the time, so I knew that when I finally worked up the courage to see the dentist, I was going to see him. I’ve had a long time fear of dental procedures, and genuinely thought my loved ones were exaggerating over how much they loved Dr. Tanner. But I was completely wrong! Dr. Tanner is hands down the best dentist I could have ever imagined, let alone have the privilege to have experienced. He was thorough, educational, and efficient. He took the time to assess all of my dental needs in one visit, never rushed, and answered each and every one of my questions to completion. Somehow my follow-up treatment visit was even better! The procedure was painless, and he once again provided excellent education regarding what to expect during the healing process. I recovered well and am now able to enjoy food again. It was genuinely an incredible experience and I will be back regularly!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"D W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcAkgQWU6RAAY7f1eOKFzWwYGH-AxV9V0yv5lVGghCNFAlbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently moved to Seattle and I was looking for a dentist that was in my plan and I do read ratings/reviews . so I went to Seattle sound downtown Seattle and I love it!!!!!\nSome of the reviews stated that the office staff was not polite. I think they’re amazing. They were nice I’m very helpful with explaining their process and everything Then I met the doctor and he is awesome personality. Nice demeanor just very caring he listens you know and he explained the process and what would need to be done for a crown and everything.\n\nI even told my son that this dentist is great so he’s gonna look him up too👍🏼😉","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelcie Pittaluga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4X2_5vhcnnU-bZa6WMWvGnhrLB76nyKrDlOLQ01ZI3JUBe1Asmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As someone with debilitating dental anxiety, I can't say enough good things about this practice and every single member of their team! I've received phenomenal care from Dr. Tanner, Jesse, and Crystal after delaying regular visits due to a cross-country move and fears surrounding finding a team patient enough to deal with my extreme anxiety, and they've quickly converted me into a patient for life. Crystal in particular deserves a special shoutout - she is an absolute angel and could not be more patient or thoughtful, doing everything possible to put me at ease. I'm incredibly grateful to have found this practice, and can't recommend them highly enough!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Armani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJt6-M_01s9ljT6CK0FeJHsG8Nscmgqy7_W-6Ta6oZzU0t7EA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went in extremely anxious due to past negative dental experiences, but the care I received completely changed that. I felt nothing but compassion and zero judgment, despite being very insecure about my teeth. A tooth that had caused me daily pain for years was saved with a root canal and crown instead of being pulled, and the result looks completely natural. I’m finally pain-free, confident enough to smile again, and no longer dread the dentist. I’m incredibly grateful to the staff and Dr. Nick Tanner for their exceptional care and highly recommend them. Special shoutout to Crystal as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ciji Munday","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDkyQHDUHSguGkrZ4Y2yoMjWuRbHkf5q2dK7dtNBoLhPNiw6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Tanner and his staff are the best! They make you feel comfortable as soon as you arrive, and are really friendly and organized. Dr. Tanner listens well and is really good at explaining options, and the work he's doing which I really appreciate.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"LightInTheDark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKI9o8jakU4qX_06H_vxzZN52dDFExzk5-iLg7JkhvHegbUnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible experience! The secretary is rude and intimidating! I went there only because I was seeing another doctor in that same building. The doctor himself is nice! However, the whole experience with this office is not worth the money and the nightmare afterwards. You pay for everything they tell you to pay for before you leave their office just to learn years later...that apparently you somehow owe them something... but it's too late because they already sued you and now the initial insignificant amount that you didn't know you owe them has quadrupled because they sued you (legal fees for court hearing you didn't know you had, no opportunity to defend yourself in anyway) and you receive a letter with court decision to put lien on your already very small paycheck. Just be aware of them practicing dishonestly, and be aware that even after you paid for everything that they told you to pay for there will be more that they will want you to  pay. Just be aware of the possibility of this scenario. There are better dental offices out there thank God!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Courtney Bay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEMevc5mN8D3CkIhgT6bLmys6JWZYUNN7HKKrh8-k17Z5icxY9ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"EDIT IN RESPONSE TO THEIR REPLY:\nIt wont let me reply to their comment but choosing to literally GASLIGHT ME and my experience by claiming I have the wrong office is insane and another reason to not support this business. Instead of taking accountability, they choose to gaslight.\n\nI never said you sent me to collections - I said the first time you made me aware of late payment was a threat to go into collections if i dont pay. My apt was in March and this didnt get resolved until August.\n\nDO NOT BOOK HERE - if they make a mistake or treat you poorly they will then choose to gaslight and deny your entire experience instead of take constructive criticism to just do better. Disgusting behavior.\n\n--------\nORIGINAL REVIEW:\nDid not have a good experience here. The dental cleaning I got took a super long time and I wasn't being rinsed/suction at all until a whole half of my mouth was polished. I was pooling in my own saliva the entire time. It was just uncomfortable and felt unprofessional.\n\nInsurance was difficult to figure out - I provided the correct information and months after my cleaning kept receiving bills for being uninsured and notices that if I didnt pay I would go into collections. The conversations I had on the phone trying to figure this out I feel were a bit rude and I felt like I was being scammed for money. My insurance carrier had told me they never received anything from the dentist all those months and I had to get my employer/company broker involved to get to a resolution.\n\nI was also recommended to get 8 fillings - this didnt feel right especially since at that point my insurance issues were unresolved and they had advised to just do the fillings and handle insurance later. And there was just no way 8 was needed when I had no issues at previous dentist. I did not move forward and got a second opinion at another dentist in the area and they told me at best I needed 2 and they werent that urgent. The new dentist told me they had absolutely no idea where anyone could have gotten 8 even if they were being nitpicky.\n\nThe doctor himself was extremely kind - so I did appreciate that. But with the reco for unneeded fillings and just overall experience with the cleaning and office staff dealing with  insurance - I would not recommend going Here","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Larry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnDrYFnW9doCk9CAG9Q8vTyD8WPE55772Nu62hRq8gU6I51A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had a mixed experience here. The staff were unclear about the actual costs, and I left unsure what I might be billed later. A friend who recommended this office ended up receiving surprise bills many months after her visit, which makes me nervous that the same could happen to me. I wish their pricing and insurance communication were more transparent up front. I had X-rays done and everything I was told looked great...a week later I had severe pain in one of my teeth that supposedly looked good on the x-ray and now I need a root canal. I'll have it done some place else now.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
