anoid=mhb967sNpen8ZWgu2EVfWQ\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=137.93098\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.gateway.dental/appointment/?utm_source=generic\u0026utm_medium=profiles\u0026utm_campaign=local_profiles","source":"gateway.dental"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"109313066588138323086","name":"Gateway Dental (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109313066588138323086"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"999 3rd Ave Plaza 18","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98104","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Joshua Mayfield","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-774uraW7AqVBxH6HZ4aAxIH8V-pLBWLlEB7B2NMxqmSpQRvv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10/10 best place for fingers in your mouth... Ok, so.. In all seriousness, the dentists and assistants here are ALL so great! I have been for an exam and multiple cleanings and had my first cavity filled here.. I'm not joking that these are the most gentle dental staff I've ever been to see. I was actually falling asleep during a deep clean I got here.\n\nI know most people despise going to the dentist, but I honestly wish everyone could experience this practice. Their front desk staff are also very nice and professional. Heck, even the billing lady is awesome!\n\nThis is not a paid advertisement. I'm not affiliated with them or any of their staff in any way. GIVE THEM YOUR BUSINESS. We should reward places like this.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly Field","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJ7vDGo9VOQlcVmjoUez8MW7rxHS7etNe9xbD7jWS_ydkQtouj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A+ Experience!\nI had such a great experience with my dentist Dr. Nealon. He was incredibly kind, patient, and attentive throughout my entire procedures. He checked in on my comfort multiple times and made sure I felt completely at ease, which I really appreciated. It’s rare to find a provider who genuinely cares about how you’re feeling in the chair, but he absolutely does. Highly recommend — A+!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sarah O'Sell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXW_S1ivMtaDNOOtJRr4KLQudrtHZb5i43TwisvVPEmA0NFjxd51w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I had to go here because I picked the wrong insurance plan not realizing that I could only go to this dentist. I thought I had already done my paperwork but it was so long ago that I answered I don't know when the receptionist asked. She then gave me 20min of papers to fill out. I got there early but then my appointment didn't start until 30min into the scheduled time. Inside during my appointment they said they did already have my insurance information - so the receptionist should have checked rather than wasting my time.\n\nAnd if I didn't fill out the pre-appointment paperwork, there could have been an automated reminder email. It's also a waste of the receptionist's time + error prone to be manually entering paperwork data.\n\nThe inside of the clinic walls and waste bins had visible grime, I was concerned for the cleanliness of the space.\n\nWhen I asked the dentist about my concerns for carcinogens in mouth guard materials (which you ingest through use), I appreciated his offer to do research for options. But then he laughed at me when I said I am also afraid of Botox so I don't want that (another option for teeth grinding). I appreciated the other notes about proactive care and long term impacts so I could be informed about procedures to invest in.\n\nOverall I give three stars because it seems like the dental staff are skilled but they are on a tight budget so there are some space, tech, and client experience things that could be improved. I appreciated the water cleaning vs. manual and the opportunity to get an oral cancer screening.\n\nThis dentist is right next to my work so this could have been an opportunity to get a new client but I am going to stick with one in my neighborhood because of the higher quality experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Teri Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKSP4qEjUrBmLh1jbUm_bzOaATws2-TXLnpJUTzC3lQnbarCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The front desk staff were helpful and kind. The hygienist was okay, seemed a bit inexperienced. The main reason, however, for the one star review was the dentist. I have had a lot of excellent dentists in the past, and this one does not live up to even an average standard.\n\nI requested to have a manual cleaning due to having sensitive teeth. The dentist tried to say that it wasn't the standard of care but he would try his best. What followed was digging at my gums and teeth in a quite erratic fashion. I was afraid he was taking off the enamel and the plaque as it was about 5x harder pressure than any other dentist I've seen in my entire life. What a weird experience. He finally hit a nerve with all of the erratic behavior and I had to stop him because I was in pain. Instead of proceeding with the torture that he chose to inflict on me, I walked out. Haven't ever had to do that before, but I knew it wasn't getting any better.\n\nThe reason I left the Midwest was to get away from brutes like him. It's interesting to run into one here in our gorgeous city, but it does happen on occasion. The dentist was trained in Texas, so I guess it's not all that surprising. I just wouldn't recommend it to anyone who actually takes care of their teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5YDdgC0RZx-zzmpfYnhHO-55eQUaXLO-tcL71EtC5o8nCgFywEw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I couldn’t be happier with Gateway Dental. I have had nothing but positive experiences. Dr. Glenn Buchanan is a terrific dentist: careful, good explainer, precise, and - to me very important - fast! Dental assistants and other staff have been, to a person, competent and confident, very reassuring. And Gateway Dental’s business office is as good as I have found in any medical office: they know how insurance works through and through, and they have helped me save money after taking the time to carefully analyze my needs. What seemed complex to me was not to them. The office location couldn’t be more convenient, right across the street from the 2nd Avenue Federal Building. No one may want to go to the dentist, but since you do have to, you may as well pick a dentist where your care will be excellent, delivered by skilled and caring professionals. I’m super glad I found Gateway Dental!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUswFv2tT3OmC8T1jJlCLfCWD7D31Lsl9CVPm4xE2kQOX_8mHBR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I very much appreciated the front desk team's patience and flexibility in working with me for my initial consultation. They were completely understanding about how I did not desire X-rays or a prophylactic cleaning for my initial consultation because I'd already had those procedures done recently. I also appreciated being made aware of the parking options in the nearby neighborhood. As for the services provided by the healthcare team, I was more than satisfied: the dynamic duo of clinician and dental assistant was wondrous, and I was put at ease very quickly. They were more than respectful of the fact that I was there primarily to obtain cost estimates for certain services that I was considering such as Reveal® clear aligners (one of only three providers of this brand in the city, as of the time of writing) and teeth whitening, and they abstained from the kind of upselling you see at a number of dental practices. These were some of the most affordable costs I've seen in my experience shopping around practices and comparing services - I'm inclined to make Gateway Dental my primary care dental practice!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshua Allen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVV7LUgdyWIg957JB4c-895XkbcUV33Qy6jh_eA8PNDnf-rL_S4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Tyler was great! Very professional and friendly. Thank you for the great work!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"CJ Rhone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPDcbZYd0v-lC4XDd0PTH9c4iLT13jE8SMlTWJGDIksxrzLn0C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"*Updated March 2023*\n\nGateway was my dentist for 4 years. You have really great dentists here who care about your teeth and go the extra mile to make sure their patients are very comfortable.\n\nHowever I am heartbroken - because midway through my crown operation, I was told to \"find another dentist\" because both Regence and Principal insurance was no longer accepted here. So yeah.. after 4 years I'm forced to find another dentist.\n\nIf you have an emergency/ pain and need professional attentiveness  for your teeth - I do recommend Gateway. However BE CAREFUL about billing, because they will dance around the subject and surprise you with a \"You owe us\". Ask lots of questions about your bill to make sure you're good.\n\n*2019*\n\nThese guys are my go to dentists 10/10 very nice and professional -- everyone who works here is lovely","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
